+# libDaisy `src/hid`
+
+## What this code is for
+
+This folder contains libDaisy's higher-level human-interface and control abstractions.
+Despite the folder name `hid`, it is **not only** about USB HID.
+It includes general-purpose input/control code such as:
+
+- switches
+- encoders
+- LEDs / RGB LEDs
+- control inputs
+- MIDI helpers and parsers
+- USB wrappers such as `usb.*`, `usb_midi.*`, and `usb_host.*`
+- audio/control helper classes used by libDaisy applications
+
+## USB-relevant files in this folder
+
+The USB-related pieces here include:
+
+- `usb.cpp` / `usb.h`
+  - libDaisy wrapper/helper layer for USB behavior
+- `usb_midi.cpp` / `usb_midi.h`
+  - USB MIDI support helpers
+- `usb_host.cpp` / `usb_host.h`
+  - USB host helper abstractions
+
+## How it works
+
+This folder sits at a more application-facing level than `src/usbd` or `src/usbh`.
+Where those folders handle lower-level middleware integration, `src/hid` provides APIs and helpers that user code can call.
+
+For example:
+
+- MIDI parser code helps interpret incoming MIDI bytes/events
+- USB helper code wraps lower-level USB setup into simpler interfaces
+- switch/encoder/LED code exposes common embedded UI controls in reusable classes
+
+## Why it matters
+
+If a libDaisy project uses USB MIDI or user-facing controls, this folder is usually part of that story.
+It is where higher-level application logic meets the lower-level USB or hardware configuration layers.
+
+## Relevance to current work
+
+RCON's current goal is a **minimal TinyUSB sample** using the **external USB port** on Daisy Seed / STM32H750 hardware.
+That means this folder is useful mainly as a reference for:
+
+- how libDaisy currently exposes USB features to applications
+- how USB MIDI is represented at a higher level
+- what parts of libDaisy would eventually need bridging if TinyUSB were integrated later
+
+For the immediate TinyUSB bring-up, this folder is not the first place to start.
+The first focus should stay on the smallest possible low-level USB enumeration path.
